# USB Guardian Task List

## Foundation
- [x] Planning & initial task breakdown
- [x] User approval on architecture plan

## Phase 1 — Core Service
- [x] Initialize `USBGuardianService` (.NET 8 Worker Service)
- [x] Implement USB blocking via Registry (`HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\USBSTOR`)
- [x] Create 5-second polling enforcement loop (`Worker.cs`)
- [x] Named Pipe IPC Server (`USBGuardianControlPipe`) in `PipeServer.cs`
- [x] Support pipe commands: `LOCK`, `UNLOCK`, `UNLOCK:<mins>`, `STATUS`, `LIST`, `ALLOW`, `BLOCK`
- [x] BCrypt password hashing and verification (`ConfigManager.cs`)
- [x] `.NET 8 WPF` Admin Control Panel (`USBGuardianControl`)
- [x] Auto-relock timer (unlock expiry logic in `UsbPolicyManager.cs`)
- [x] `Install-Background-Service.bat` — registers service as auto-start LocalSystem

## Phase 2 — Granular Hub-Level Control
- [x] Migrate from registry-based blocking to native `pnputil.exe` hub disabling
- [x] WMI `Win32_PnPEntity` query targeting USB Root Hubs
- [x] Individual hub Allow/Block toggle in UI and pipe protocol
- [x] Fix conflict between Master Unlock/Lock and granular allow/block lists
- [x] Fix deadlock caused by PowerShell → moved to pure `pnputil` + async `Task.Run`

## Phase 3 — Cleanup & Documentation
- [x] Remove all temporary diagnostic/logging scripts
- [x] Write `README.md` with full architecture and deployment guide
- [x] Write `ChangeManagement.md` with phase-by-phase development ledger

## Phase 4 — Security Hardening: Change Password
- [x] Add `ChangePassword()` method to `ConfigManager.cs`
- [x] Add `CHANGEPASSWORD` command to `PipeServer.cs` pipe protocol
- [x] Create `ChangePasswordWindow.xaml` modal popup
- [x] Create `ChangePasswordWindow.xaml.cs` code-behind with input validation
- [x] Add `⚙ Change Password` ghost button to auth row in `MainWindow.xaml`
- [x] Fix broken `Grid.Row` layout (overlapping System Master Policy and Granular Device Control)
- [x] Update `Update-Service.bat` to also publish `USBGuardianControl` UI

## Phase 5 — Two-Layer Lock Enforcement
- [x] Identify security gap: force-eject already-mounted USB drives on lock
- [x] Add `ForceEjectActiveUsbDevices()` — disables `USBSTOR%` + USB MTP/phone devices
- [x] Identify follow-on bug: disabled USBSTOR devices don't recover on unlock
- [x] Add `ForceEnableUsbDevices()` — re-enables disabled USBSTOR/MTP on unlock
- [x] Refactor both into `ApplyToUsbChildDevices()` shared helper
- [x] `Enforce()` now fully symmetric: lock → eject, unlock → re-enable

## Phase 6 — UI: Connected Device Indicators & PC Hostname
- [x] Show PC hostname (`Environment.MachineName`) below panel title
- [x] Extend `UsbDeviceInfo` model with `IsHub` and `ConnectedDeviceName` fields
- [x] Extend `GetConnectedDevices()` with second WMI pass for `USBSTOR` + MTP devices
- [x] Add `IsHub`, `HubRowVisibility`, `DeviceRowVisibility`, `ConnectedLabel`, `ConnectedColor` to `UsbDeviceViewModel`
- [x] Dual-template device list in `MainWindow.xaml`:
  - Hub rows: `⬡` icon, policy badge, Allow/Block buttons
  - Connected device rows: `🔌` icon, indented, colour-coded CONNECTED/BLOCKED badge
